6: So this is your new place!
10:
My home and new office. Make
yourselves at home.
14:
Gotta say, never expected you to
become a handyman.
18:
It's kinda weird to see you out of
your military uniform.
31:
After leaving the military, I needed
to find a way to make a living
somehow.
34:
With my skills, I should be able to get
by here.
39:
Not a bad way to earn an income, in
all honesty. It's kind of like us taking
odd jobs in Palpebra.
43:
Right. Pretty similar, actually. I'm
sure you see jobs like this all the
time.
48:
A request to find a lost cat named...
Catherine?
53:
Oh yeah, we've definitely had our
share of lost pet jobs. They always
end up a lot more troublesome than
you'd think.
57:
Someone in the neighborhood
made the request. If you spot her
while you're here, do let me know.
62:
Expanding your network of intel,
huh? Smart.
67:
If I may... Why not become an
adventurer in Palpebra instead?
70: The work is a lot more steady there.
75:
Maybe doing that every once in a
while wouldn't be bad.
79:
But I'd like to make my roots here.
I'm a man of the sea. Can't live
without hearing the waves outside.
87:
If we can help out in any way, just let
us know.
102: Whew, we sure talked for a while.
106:
I would've cooked dinner, but I'm
afraid I'm awful in the kitchen.
109:
But I know a good bistro around
these parts. Why don't we have a
bite there?
123:
Ah! That cat looks exactly like the
one on the flyer!
127:
Hmm... She should be around here...
But where'd she go?
131:
You know, this Float has... quite the
unique charm to it.
135:
You find this worn-out, rusty heap of
metal "charming"?
140: I-I was trying to be polite!
145:
This Float is pretty far from the
capital. It's fairly old and doesn't see
much maintenance done.
148:
Which means an outcast like me
won't stick out here.
152:
I see. It's a relatively quiet place,
which I suppose makes it
comfortable to live in.
163:
Wait. Something about this place
seems off.
167:
Yeah, something's definitely not
right... You think they're pirates?
171:
Doubt they're upstanding citizens,
that's for sure.
176:
Why don't we have ourselves a
closer look?
180:
F-fine by me... But why do you sound
so excited about it?
188:
People used to make jewelry out of
the stuff, but nobody's allowed to
collect more of it nowadays.
195:
You moron! Don't damage the
goods! Or are you tryin' ta get
yerself shot in the head?
208:
Now, now. Let's be calm about this.
Sorry for entering without knocking.
211:
Oh, you think you're funny, do ya? I'll
show you funny! Get 'em, lads!
215: Well, no way around it now.
220:
What do you say to a little dance
class before dinner?
223: Urgh... Wh-who in the world are you?
226:
Just a handyman out looking for a
lost cat. I just started my business
recently.
231:
Eat as much as you like! Consider it
the least I can do after you went
and found my dear Catherine!
235:
Hey, you! I heard all about how you
secretly took out those coral
poachers!
237:
Ain't that something! Y'know, if I ever
need anything done, I'll be sure to
come to you!
240:
Guess things are about to get lively
for you, huh?
244: I think that's a good thing.
249:
Haha! What happened to not
sticking out and living all quiet-like?
257:
I think I could get used to living like
this instead.
